# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1807-in-the-united-states
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] The **10th United States Congress** was a meeting of the legislative branch of the United States federal government, consisting of the Senate and the House of Representatives.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] It met in Washington, D.C., from March 4, 1807, to March 4, 1809, during the seventh and eighth years of Thomas Jefferson's presidency.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] The apportionment of seats in the House of Representatives was based on the 1800 census; both chambers had an overwhelming Democratic-Republican majority.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] The count below identifies party affiliations at the beginning of the first session of this Congress.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] Changes resulting from subsequent replacements are shown below in the "Changes in membership" section.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] This list is arranged by chamber, then by state.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] Senators are listed in order of seniority, and representatives are listed by district.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] Senators were elected by the state legislatures every two years, with one-third beginning new six-year terms with each Congress.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] Preceding the names in the list below are Senate class numbers, which indicate the cycle of their election.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] The names of representatives are preceded by their district numbers.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] The count below reflects changes from the beginning of the first session of this Congress.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] There were 5 resignations, 2 deaths, and 1 interim appointment.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] Of the voting members, there were 4 resignations, 4 deaths, and 2 vacancies from the beginning of this Congress.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] Democratic-Republicans had no net change and Federalists picked up 2 seats.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/10th-united-states-congress] Lists of committees and their party leaders.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/1776-in-the-united-states] 1776 is celebrated in the United States as the official beginning of the nation, with the Declaration of Independence of the Thirteen Colonies from the British Empire issued on July 4.
[src:1807-in-the-united-states/1807-in-the-united-states] Events from the year **1807 in the United States**.
